Purchase Order Creation Copilot (D365 F&O)
This repository contains the source definitions for a custom Copilot Studio agent designed to automate Purchase Order (PO) creation within Microsoft Dynamics 365 Finance and Operations (USMF).

Overview
The agent acts as an intelligent assistant capable of extracting procurement data from various inputs—including free-text, PDF documents, and images—to streamline the creation of Purchase Orders while ensuring data integrity and mandatory user validation.

Features
Multi-Modal Input: Automatically detects and processes PO details from text, PDFs, or image-based sales quotes.

F&O Integration: Utilizes Data, API, and Form tools to interact directly with D365 F&O.

Vendor Resolution: Performs intelligent fuzzy matching against the USMF vendor database, ensuring only valid, active vendors are used.

Mandatory Confirmation: Requires a clear "Yes" from the user after presenting a comprehensive summary before executing any create operations.

Strict Governance: Hard-coded to the USMF legal entity to prevent cross-entity data errors.

Error Handling: Provides clear, non-technical alerts if processes fail (e.g., missing items, OData errors, or validation issues).

Architecture
The agent is built using the following core components:

Data Tools: Primary method for all CRUD operations using OData (e.g., PurchaseOrderHeadersV2).

Form/API Tools: Fallback methods for UI interaction and specific X++ logic.

Reasoning Layer: Step-by-step reflection following every tool call to ensure accuracy.

Workflow
Detection: Identify input type and extract fields (Vendor, Dates, Line Items, Currency).

Verification: Verify vendor status in USMF.

Summary: Present a full order summary for user approval.

Creation: Perform creation in D365 only upon explicit confirmation.

Reset: Clear all session data post-creation to ensure privacy and readiness for the next request.

Development Standards
Naming Conventions: Uses system menu, control, and tab names (never labels).

OData Best Practices: Uses plural entity names and specific Enum filter formats (e.g., $filter=Style has Namespace.Pattern'Value').

Version Control: This repository serves as the source of truth for the agent's logic. All changes should be synced via the Copilot Studio VS Code extension and committed to the main branch.

Contributing
To contribute changes:

Clone the agent using the Copilot Studio VS Code extension.

Modify the relevant .yml topic or configuration files.

Validate changes in the Copilot Studio testing pane.

Commit changes and push to this repository.

Use the "Apply Changes" feature in the extension to sync your local updates back to the Power Platform environment.

Note: This agent is strictly configured for the USMF legal entity. Attempting to redirect it to other entities is unsupported.
